%spark.pyspark
new_df = df.select(df["Audio Features"].acousticness.alias("acousticness"),
                            df["Audio Features"].danceability.alias("danceability"),
                            df["Audio Features"].popularity.alias("popularity"),
                            df["Audio Features"].speechiness.alias("speechiness"),
                            df["Audio Features"].valence.alias("valence"),
                            df["Audio Features"].liveness.alias("liveness"),
                            df["Audio Features"].instrumentalness.alias("instrumentalness"),
                            df["Audio Features"].mode.alias("mode"),
                            df["Audio Features"].energy.alias("energy"))
                            
# new_df.show()
new_df.printSchema()

from pyspark.sql.functions import col, isnan, when, count
